Research, Stress, and Hate all mixed into one<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Kelranon sat at his desk, constantly writing, showing no attention to anything else around him. He was in his most favorite place in Norrath...his laboratory. He scribbled and took notes, and read through his books at least 5 times each. His skeletal maid pet bent over to see what he was doing. Quickly Kelranon turned around and blasted her into a few bone chips.<br>
<br>
&quot;Worthless pile of bones,&quot; he muttered, and continued his work. He stood up and walked over to his cutting board and placed a large bat on it. The bat squeeled and hissed at the necromancer, as he used his dagger to remove both its wings.<br>
&quot;Now now, that wasn't so hard was it?&quot; Kelranon laughed at the helpless fool and threw him out the window to his dogs.<br>
Deciding to take a break, he walked around his house, checking to make sure his slaves were doing their work properly. <br>
<br>
He stepped into the kitchen, pleased to see his vampiric slaves cutting him up something to eat, he stepped over to the restroom and was pleased that his skeletons were cleaning it properly, then made sure the bed was nice and neat, which it was. This relieved Kelranon's stress by a lot. He looked out the windows and saw his zombie troopers were defending his house properly, so he laid back, and rested. <br>
&quot;I will be the librarian,&quot; he'd keep telling himself. Hate grew strong in his heart. But suddenly, the door burst open. Very upset at the intrusion of his house, Kelranon stepped downstairs. He saw a messenger drop off a book. Kelranon gave him a few more platinum then it was worth for the tip, then picked up the book.<br>
<br>
&quot;By Innoruuk, it's here!&quot; He grinned evilly as he opened the book. But to his surprise, it was in a language totally foreign to him. He screamed at the top of his lungs in anger. How could this be? he thought to himself. I ordered this book with the assurance I'd be able to translate it!<br>
<br>
&quot;DAMMIT, now I have to go find my book of languages,&quot; he shouted at himself. He walked back over to his desk and ripped out a book entitled, &quot;The Combine Empire and the Languages That Follow.&quot; <br>
<br>
Love and Hate, both a weapon, both a tool, I use both for Innoruuk and my loved.<br>
