-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Creapiing looks around her ravaged offices and hears the echoes of her footsteps on the empty floors. New furniture had been ordered, new shelves would be built by morning. The beautiful Mahogany desk could never be replaced, nor could all the ancient tomes, art works, and tapestries. Her knees suddenly felt weak as the poison again attacked her, and she leaned heavily on the wall for a moment. Then as the weakness passed she stood up to see her assistant bringing a scroll. Quickly ripping it open she sees incribed on the scroll one name...Kelranon.<br>
<br>
She turned to leave, to seek out this Kelranon..for she had many many books to replace, or at least to find some mockery of them, as many had been simply irreplacable. <br>
