-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
What do you want? boomed throughout the house. With a wry smile Creapiing ignored all the theatrics and spoke, Let us speak over a chill glass of this red wine that I have brought with me. Surely you have a nice shadowed room in which we may speak?<br>
<br>
Kelranon wondered to himself..the Reaper of the Harvest..in my home! What have I done to deserve such a visit? Carefully setting aside the tome he had been diligently translating, he approached the Reaper and noted the precise way in which she bowed to him. Dark Sister, how may I help you?Kelranon asked.<br>
<br>
Creapiings violet eyes were a bit unsettling as she handed him a very fine red wine and beckoned him to show her to a more comfortable speaking room. <br>
<br>
Kelranon, I have heard from the finest sources that you keep a library worthy of Faellen K'this herself. With the gutting of my home and offices to try and find the source of my poisoning, I am in great need of both reference material and manuscripts. I would not like to see myself fall into the trap of ignorance that the pale ones so often stumble into, and therefore I must surround myself with knowledge.<br>
<br>
The third glass of wine was poured, and Creapiing and Kelranon sat comfortably trying to work out the specifics of her needs.  <br>
